 deal, and both the board and Agrawal might have figured they=E2=80=99d get=
 sued personally if they didn=E2=80=99t get the deal closed. Still, I think=
 there was a lot of room for compromise, and a CEO dead-set on remaining in=
dependent could have maybe negotiated a settlement with Musk =E2=80=94 one =
that involved Musk not buying Twitter =E2=80=94 and then sold it to the boa=
rd and shareholders.


  [3] Oh, I kid, would you take Elon Musk=E2=80=99s personal note?


